      • analyze

        public static ClawPragma analyze(Xnode pragma)
                          throws IllegalDirectiveException
        Analyze a raw string input and match it with the CLAW language definition.
        Parameters:
        pragma - A raw pragma element object to be analyzed against the CLAW language.
        Returns:
        A ClawPragma object with the corresponding extracted information.
        Throws:
        IllegalDirectiveException - If directive does not follow the CLAW language specification.

      • createLoopFusionLanguage

        public static ClawPragma createLoopFusionLanguage(ClawPragma master)
        Create an instance of ClawPragma that correspond to a loop-fusion directive. Used for dynamically created transformation.
        Parameters:
        master - Base object which initiate the creation of this instance.
        Returns:
        An instance of ClawPragma describing a loop-fusion with the group, collapse clauses and the pragma from the master object.

        Create an instance of ClawPragma that correspond to a loop-interchange directive. Used for dynamically created transformation.
        Parameters:
        master - Base object which initiate the creation of this instance.
        pragma - Pragma statement located just before the first do stmt.
        Returns:
        An instance of ClawPragma describing a loop-interchange with the indexes from the master object.
